method.name: emulation_ancp_config
method.description: This procedure will configure ANCP devices on an Ixia port.

description.text: Access Node Control Protocol (ANCP) Standard followed by implementation. For Ixia this is either ietf-ancp-protocol5 or rfc6320. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = rfc6320)
The Gateway IP address of the Access Node. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 0.0.0.0)
The incrementing step for the Gateway IP address. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 0.0.0.0)
Enable Port Down rate settings

The number of Port Down event messages to send each second. This is a global level setting. When events_per_interval is present, then this option is ignored. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 50)
Port down rate interval in milliseconds
Port down rate max outstanding
Indicates whether the control is specified per port or per device group
Enable Port Up rate settings

The number of Port Up event messages to send each second. This is a global level setting. When events_per_interval is present, then this option is ignored. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 10)
Port Up rate interval in milliseconds
Port Up rate max outstanding
Indicates whether the control is specified per port or per device group
Enable ANCP Start rate settings
ANCP Start rate
ANCP Start rate interval in milliseconds
ANCP Start rate max outstanding
Indicates whether the control is specified per port or per device group
Enable ANCP Stop rate settings
ANCP Stop rate
ANCP Stop rate interval in milliseconds
ANCP Start rate max outstanding
Indicates whether the control is specified per port or per device group

When mode is create this is the parent handle used for creating this object. It can be a topology, or a device group, or an ethernet or an ipv4. Other modes require an ancp handle returned by ::ixngpf::emulation_ancp_config.
The IP address of the Access Node. It doesn't support a list of IP Addresses. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 10.10.10.2)
The prefix length for the IP address of the interface address (Access Node address). This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 16)
Step value for incrementing interface address. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 0.0.0.1)

The time period (in hundreads of milli seconds) between the sending two keep alive messages. Specify the value in multiple of 1000. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 10000)

The number of NAS Keep-Alive retries. If a Keep-Alive times out, the emulated access node will re-send it the number of times specified by this parameter before determining that the connection to the NAS has gone down. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 3)
Limit the Number of attempts to establish ANCP adjacency in case connection is lost
Number of attempts to establish ANCP adjacency in case connection is lost
To enable/disable line configuration capabilities. For Ixia, this is always 0. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 0)
Enable/Disable DSL Remote Line Conectivity Testing Capability
Defines starting local MAC address (Access Node MAC address). This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 000a.0a00.0200)
Incrementing step for local MAC address (Access Node MAC address). This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 0000.0000.0001)

Action to perform. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = create) Valid choices are: create - Create new ANCP range on -port_handle or -handle(DHCP, PPP, IP endpoint). Parameter -port_handle takes priority when both

restriction.value: create modify delete enable disable enable_all disable_all

description.text: SUT address of the test interface/emulated ANCP. The IP address of the NAS to which the emulated access node is connected. It cannot support a list of IP addresses. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 20.20.0.1)
The NAS ANCP TCP service port number. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 6068)
Enable/disable topology discovery functionality. For Ixia, this will always be 1. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 1)
Enable/Disable advertise Transactional Multicast capability
Vlan ID for Access Node. Doesn't support a list of vlan IDs. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork.
Defines the Inner Vlan ID for Access Node. Doesn't support a list of vlan IDs. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork.
Defines the Vlan ID incrementing step. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 1)
Defines the Inner Vlan ID incrementing step. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 1)
Defines the Vlan user priority for Access Node. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 0)
Defines the Inner Vlan user priority for Access Node. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 0)
Partition ID to be used in adjacency negotiation

Enable sending Port Up/Port Down events when AN is Started/Stopped. Does not apply if flapping is enabled on the Access Loop. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxTclNetwork. (DEFAULT = 0)

returnValue.value: A list containing the ancp protocol stack handles that were added by the command (if any).
When status is failure, contains more information.
The list of ANCP handles configured. Please note that this key will be omitted if the current session or command were run with -return_detailed_handles 0.

notes.note: 1) Unsupported parameters or unsupported parameter options will be silently ignored. If the current session or command was run with -return_detailed_handles 0 the following keys will be omitted from the command response: handle
